cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper discusses the impact of constrained reservoir topologies in the architectural design of deep reservoirs, which is a topic related to neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the performance gain achieved by the synergy between a deep reservoir construction and a structured organization of the recurrent units in each layer, which is related to deep learning and could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions numerical experiments on several RC benchmarks, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
